header.gameNote: LOU HENSON AWARD TOURNAMENT AT ROCHESTER MI

article.headline: E. Michigan 82, Rochester, Mich. 63
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Brandon Bowdry finished with 22 points and 14 rebounds as Eastern Michigan defeated Rochester College 82-63 for third place in the Lou Henson Award Holiday Tournament on Tuesday night. Kamil Janton came off the bench to add 11 points for the Eagles (2-9), who snapped an eight-game losing streak. Michael Graham led the Warriors (8-7) with 11 points and Lawrence Hicks had 10. Eastern Michigan took a 43-31 lead into halftime and slowly added on to its advantage in the second half. The Eagles outrebounded the Warriors 53-31 and hit 10 3-pointers.
